  "legislative_session": "20252026",
  "identifier": "SB1287",
  "title": "Personal Income Tax Law: Corporation Tax Law: credits: shortline railroad expenditures and railroad infrastructure.",
  "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}",
  "classification": [
    "bill"
  ],
  "subject": [
    "CorporationTaxLaw",
    "PersonalIncomeTaxLaw",
    "credits",
    "shortlinerailroadexpendituresandrailroadinfrastructure"
  ],
  "abstracts": [
    {
      "note": "summary",
      "abstract": "The Personal Income Tax Law and the Corporation Tax Law allow various credits against the taxes imposed by those laws.\n\nThis bill, the Shortline Railroad Modernization Act of 2026, would allow credits against those taxes for each taxable year beginning on or after January 1, 2027, and before January 1, 2032, to a qualified taxpayer in an amount equal to 50% of the qualified shortline railroad expenditures and for each taxable year beginning on or after January 1, 2028, and before January 1, 2033, in an amount equal to 50% of the qualified new rail infrastructure expenditures, as defined and specified.\n\nExisting law requires a bill authorizing a new tax expenditure to contain, among other things, specific goals, purposes, and objectives the tax expenditure will achieve, detailed performance indicators, and data collection requirements.\n\nThis bill would include additional information required for any bill authorizing a new tax expenditure.\n\nThis bill would take effect immediately as a tax levy."
    }
  ],
